BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Blind Spot: How Oligarchs Dominate Our Democracies | Buffett B
 ook Talk with Jeffrey Winters
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260515T173000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260515T184500Z
UID:089b25a2c75f2146a2ee0361297bc59e@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:From ancient empires to modern nation-states\, extreme concent
 rations of wealth have shaped political power—but never quite like this.
  Today\, the influence of oligarchs is exercised not in opposition to demo
 cracy\, but through it. Even as inequality reaches historic extremes\, dem
 ocratic systems continue to function\, and public revolt remains muted. Wh
 y do societies repeatedly vote to sustain arrangements that entrench their
  own exclusion?\nJoin us for a Buffett Book Talk with Jeffrey A. Winters\,
  Professor of Political Science\, Director of the Roberta Buffett Institut
 e’s Equality Development & Globalization Studies (EDGS) Program\, and au
 thor of The Blind Spot: How Oligarchs Dominate Our Democracies. In convers
 ation with Edward L. Gibson\, Kenneth Burgess Professor of Political Scien
 ce\, Winters will trace the evolution of oligarchy in the democratic era\,
  arguing that the outsized power of the ultra-wealthy is not a breakdown o
 f democracy but a feature embedded in its design. They will examine Winter
 s’ concept of participatory inequality—a paradoxical condition in whic
 h nearly everyone participates freely in democratic processes\, yet only a
  tiny fraction exercises meaningful economic and political power—and off
 er ideas for how societies might rebalance power and pursue more equitable
  futures.\nLunch will begin at 12:15 p.m.\nCo-sponsored by the Department 
 of Political Science.\nPlease note that 720 University Place is not an ADA
 -accessible space. Increasing physical access to buildings and facilities 
 is a goal of the University\, but not all buildings and venues have been u
 pdated.
LOCATION:720 University Place\, 720 University Place\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/638862
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University (Community)
END:VEVENT
